Sentencas: (PrBa)(0.95)Mn1.9Ru0.1O5+delta (PBMRu) layered double perovskite is turned into a highly active electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells (SSOFCs) by introducing Ru/RuO2 catalysts through in situ growth, which demonstrates excellent electrochemical properties as both oxygen and fuel electrodes.
Titulo: In Situ Growth of Ru/RuO2 Nanoparticle-Modified (PrBa)0.95Mn1.9Ru0.1O5+δ as a High-Performance Electrode for Symmetrical Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The catalytically active Ru nanoparticles exsolve during the reducing step of the preparation process and can be oxidized to nanosized RuO2 catalysts when operating as an oxygen electrode.
Titulo: In Situ Growth of Ru/RuO2 Nanoparticle-Modified (PrBa)0.95Mn1.9Ru0.1O5+δ as a High-Performance Electrode for Symmetrical Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Optimized by substitutional Ru and in situ nanosized Ru/RuO2 catalysts, the favorable electrical conductivities of 14.89 and 146.81 S cm(-1) are possessed for PBMRu in 5% H-2/N-2 and air at 750 degrees C, which are much higher than 7.83 and 90.76 S cm(-1) of (PrBa)(0.95)Mn2O5+delta (PBM).
Titulo: In Situ Growth of Ru/RuO2 Nanoparticle-Modified (PrBa)0.95Mn1.9Ru0.1O5+δ as a High-Performance Electrode for Symmetrical Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: With Ru and RuO2 nanoparticles on the two sides of the cell, respectively, symmetrical single-cell PBMRu-SSZ|SSZ|PBMRu-SSZ (SSZ = Sc2O3-stabilized ZrO2) exhibits an outstanding output performance of 0.92 W cm(-2) at 750 degrees C. All of these findings suggest that in situ Ru/RuO2 nanocatalyst-modified PBMRu would be a promising candidate for an electrode in high-performance SSOFC applications.
Titulo: In Situ Growth of Ru/RuO2 Nanoparticle-Modified (PrBa)0.95Mn1.9Ru0.1O5+δ as a High-Performance Electrode for Symmetrical Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
